How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Sylvia
5.0 out of 5 stars Read and Heed Warning!
Reviewed in the United States on August 13, 2015
Verified Purchase
Excellent, easy to read and considering the original was written in the 1970's it is as if you are reading today's headlines. David Wilkerson is definitely a profit from God and America is in Big Trouble. We are in the "birth pangs" of the "last days" as the Bible says and as David Wilkerson says and it is good to get some clear insight that is even more culturally relevant and timely now than when the book was written. Anyone living in the current generation, especially the Milennials should read this and take heed. Call upon the name of the Lord, confess your sins, thank Jesus of Nazareth for taking the sins of the world(past, present and future) upon himself and being the substitutionary sacrifice for your personal sins so you don't have to suffer the penalty yourself with God's Wrath which is closer now than ever before. Thank God for this. I have written on nearly every page the events that have been fulfilled as he has described in his vision. It is truly amazing. Share with your Pastor, Small Group, Bible Study, Prayer Partners, Family and Friends. They don't teach Biblical truth or prophecy like this anymore in most churches. If nothing else this will/should prompt an interest to dig deeper into what the Bible says about what David Wilkerson says. Always check it out against Biblical Scripture so you are not deceived.
